<HEADLINE> Chinese Leaders Attend New Year Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leaders joined more
than 10,000 people this evening in Beijing's Great Hall of the
People to celebrate the Chinese Lunar New Year, which falls on
January 28 this year.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing, both members of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, joined senior officials and other people
for a round of performance by well-known Chinese artists, which
included Beijing opera pieces, song and dance items, and
acrobatics. The Beijing Opera Troupe drew an enthusiastic response
from opera lovers with an excellent show.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hall of the People also provided special puppet shows
and entertainment for children.  
</P>
</TEXT>
