<HEADLINE> Sykora Wins Men's Slalom in Kitzbuehel of Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Austria's Thomas Sykora won a
men's World Cup slalom Monday in a combined time of oen munite
52.81 second but Norway's 22-year-old Hans-Petter Buraas set
himself an Olympic target after coming second in Kitzbuehel of
Austria
</P>
<P>
Buraas, fastest in the first run ahead of Sykora, had to be
satisfied with a best-ever second place in the World Cup in
1:52.99.
</P>
<P>
The next slalom is the Olympic race in Nagano.
</P>
<P>
Lillehammer Olympic champion Thomas Stangassinger of Austria,
who won his third slalom this season in Kitzbuehel on Sunday, shot
up from 15th after the first run to third in 1:53.79. 
</P>
</TEXT>
