<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Government Bans LTTE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
banned the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), an official
announced a short while ago Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The official said the LTTE is outlawed now.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting with the government troops in an
effort to create a separate state of their own in the north and
east.
</P>
<P>
The decision came one day after a bomb exploded at Kandy,
killing 12 people and damaging a place of worship of Sri Lankan
Buddhists, the Tooth Relic Temple, Sunday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
