<DOCNO> XIE19980127.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Urges Openness, Transparency in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 26 (Xinhua) -- European Union foreign
ministers today urged the Algerian government to show "greater
transparency" over the recent massacres that claimed thousands of
lives in the north African country.
</P>
<P>
"The EU demands greater transparency by the Algerian
government, especially with regard to the situation in which
terrorist groups continue to perpetrate cowardly and brutal
attacks on innocent civilians," an EU spokesman told the press.
</P>
<P>
The EU foreign ministers were holding a general affairs council
meeting which was scheduled to also deal with issues of EU
enlargement and the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers called on Algeria to allow the United
Nations officials to visit the country to help end the wave of
violence.
</P>
<P>
An EU troika mission travelled to Algeria last week. The
mission at ministerial level was sent after Algeria refused to
receive an earlier proposal of an EU troika mission of mid-level
officials.
</P>
<P>
Robin Cook, foreign secretary of Britain that is serving the
rotating presidency of the 15-nation union, said that the troika
mission was sent in the hope of finding out if there was anything
the union could do to help.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether an Algerian foreign ministry official would
be invited to go to London for further discussions, the British
foreign secretary said that no date was set for it.
</P>
<P>
"Our willingness to help needs to have response from the
Algerian government," Cook told a press briefing in between the
sessions of the foreign ministers meeting.
</P>
<P>
The EU troika mission was led by Derek Fatchett, minister of
state from the British Foreign Office. The Troika also includes
ministers from Luxembourg and Austria.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, up to 70,000 people have been killed in
the Algerian civil war between government forces and Islamic
fundamentalists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
