<HEADLINE> IBCA's Ratings Assigned To SPC Credit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Fitch IBCA, the international
rating agency assigned ratings today to Hongkong's SPC Credit Ltd
at a long-term rating of A+ and a short-term rating of F1.
</P>
<P>
The Individual rating is B/C, reflecting the bank's
satisfactory performance and risks profile, while the Legal rating
of 3 indicates the agnecy's expectation of shareholder support,
and important factor behind the security ratings.
</P>
<P>
This is Fitch IBCA's first rating of a restricted lilcense bank
since Hongkong's return to Chinese sovereignty in July 1997.
</P>
<P>
SPC Credit is a Restricted license Bank established in 1974. It
was initially owned by Security Pacific Corporation and became a
subsidiary of Bank of America after the merger between Security
Pacific and the bank.
</P>
<P>
SPC Credit's focus is on consumer finance and small business
lending in Hongkong, and expanding its consumer finance business
in Asia.
</P>
<P>
IBCA said, like other lenders in Hongkong, SPC Credit has been
affected by volatile Hongkong dollar interest rates and faces a
more challenging economic environment.
</P>
<P>
The bank is, however, currently in sound shape and has a good
record of profitability and asset quality, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
