The Ugandan people now govern their country through national
elections, and these elections were very rare before the NRM
government took power, Museveni said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has witnessed three elections in the past 24 years.
After the Ugandan people elected their parliament and the
president in 1996, another local election is under way, he
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The president urged his people to carefully exercise their
right to elect their candidates.
</P>
<P>
Nelson Mandela, the South African President, also delivered a
short speech on the occasion, saying that Africa's renaissance
can reach its full when every African has his or her political
and economic freedom.
</P>
<P>
He regretted that there are still too many Africans who do not
enjoy real freedom, and are forced to live in poverty, illiteracy
and diseases.
</P>
<P>
Mandela, who arrived here for a one-day visit, is the main
guest at the celebrations. 
