<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Increase Rice Exports to Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's rice exports,
mainly to Europe, are expected to reach 600 million U.S. dollars
in the current fiscal year, 100 million dollars more than the set
annual target, the Commerce Ministry predicts.
</P>
<P>
The demand for Pakistani rice has risen in the international
market, particularly in Europe, the ministry says.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official figures, Pakistan's rice
exports during the first half of the 1997-98 fiscal year starting
July 1 rose by 7.45 percent to 210.11 million dollars as against
195.54 million dollars in the previous corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
As the European Union (EU) has lifted the restriction on the
quantity of Pakistani rice to be exported to European countries
this year, the country's exports are expected to grow to around
25,000 to 30,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The EU had limited the export amount of Pakistani rice to 9,000
tons last year before lifting the unilateral restriction after the
Pakistani government lodged a strong protest last November.
</P>
</TEXT>
