<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, UK to Hold Cooperation Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe and the United Kingdom
will in February stage a series of trade fairs, seminars and
cultural events to promote and strengthen economic ties between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
British High Commissioner to Zimbabwe Martin Williams told a
press conference at his residence in Harare Monday that the
UK/Zimbabwe Cooperation Week would be one of the largest
bilateral events in Zimbabwe's history.
</P>
<P>
Harare, the capital, and Bulawayo, Zimbabwe's second largest
city, would host the multi-faceted event from February 3 to 7
with "partnership and progress" as the general theme.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Zimbabwe's land reform program, the High
Commissioner said it was true there were differences between
Britain and Zimbabwe over some aspects of the program, but
discussions were taking place to see how the differences could be
narrowed.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe is set to confiscate big white farms to distribute
plots of land to poor African peasants and the move is frowned on
by Britain. 
</P>
