<HEADLINE> Nigeria Plans Mass Vaccination Against Yellow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Health Minister Rear
Admiral Jubril Ayinla said here Monday his ministry plans to
vaccinate every Nigerian against yellow fever.
</P>
<P>
The government has directed that everybody should be
vaccinated against the disease, said the minister, quoted by the
News Agency of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The federal government and other agencies responsible for
health matters will fund the national program, he said without
giving the cost of the proposed nationwide vaccination.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the program will be carried out in
conjunction with the national health care agency and other bodies
responsible for disease control in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said the government would continue to focus attention on
the primary health care system since "prevention is better than
cure".
</P>
<P>
Currently, the government was focusing attention on primary
health care for the rural dwellers because people with "little
education are prone to diseases than those who have basic
knowledge of how to prevent diseases", the minister added.
</P>
