at the conference in view of LCD leader and Prime Minister Ntsu
Mokhehle's decision to leave the government.
</P>
<P>
It was not known whether or not Mokhehle would also stand down
as party leader. "Should he decide he is relinquishing the
position, that means the meeting will have to find a
replacement," Moleleki said. 
