<HEADLINE> Parliament Cooperation Agreement Signed by Russia, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 26 (Xinhua) -- An agreement on cooperation was
signed Monday by the Russian State Duma and the Tajik parliament,
according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The accord is part of State Duma chairman Gennady Seleznyov's
official visit to Tajikistan. Seleznyov arrived in Dushanbe,
capital of Tajikistan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to develop relations with each other and
promote contacts in such fields as human rights, ethnic relations,
regional policy, culture, education, environment and other areas
of humanitarian cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They also intended to facilitate work to draft laws on economic
cooperation, the document said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after the signing ceremony,
Seleznyov said that the two countries have virtually limitless
prospects for economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that Russia should support Tajikistan's accession
to the Customs Union as an important step in developing such
cooperative relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the Russian peacekeeping forces in Tajikistan, Seleznyov
said that the Russian forces are the only guarantor of stability
in that country. But he agreed that the Russian peacekeepers
should be gradually withdrawn from Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Tajik National Reconciliation Commission to
continue its work.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik authorities and its opposition signed the General
Agreement on Peace and National Concord in Moscow in June 1997 and
there is still need to continue the dialogue between the two sides
within the framework of the Commission for National
Reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov is to inspect a border post on January 27, where
Tajik and Russian troops are guarding the border between
Tajikistan and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that bilateral accords are planned to be signed
at the end of the visit of the Russian delegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
