<HEADLINE> Eritrean Resolution on Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The ministers in Eritrea
have adopted a resolution on popular participation in
agricultural production, the latest issue of the English weekly
''Eritrea Profile'' reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said, the resolution was adopted at a meeting held
last Thursday when the cabinet of ministers discussed the work
plans of the Ministry of Agriculture for 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the ministers underlined the vital
significance of popular participation in efforts to effectively
implement agricultural development programs planned for this
year.
</P>
<P>
In line with the decision passed by the cabinet, the report
said, the envisaged popular participation will take effect before
the onset of the rainy season from June to September and the
scheme will be applied yearly, taking into account the
experiences acquired in the process.
</P>
<P>
The meeting stressed that efforts will be mounted to raise
agricultural production on the basis of the application of modern
inputs, alongside steps to ensure the productivity of the
traditional farming sector.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it is planned that demonstration plots in various
locations will be selected for the purpose of modern agricultural
development projects.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the meeting decided that peasant farmers will be
encouraged and assisted to take part in marketing their produce
through the mechanism of cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea had poor harvests in agriculture for the last two
years due to droughts in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
