<HEADLINE> Kigali Wants Rwandan Refugees Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government has
reiterated its desire to have all its refugees remaining outside
the country return to the motherland, according to a RNA special
dispatch to Xinhua here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
"The Rwandan government is not going to leave a single stone
unturned to ensure that these people, whether they are innocent
or not, return home," the Chairman of the Government commission
for Repatriation Kabaija (only name) was quoted by Rwanda News
Agency (RNA) as saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kabaija was reacting to the case of about 12,000 Rwandan Hutu
refugees in two refugee camps in Congo (B) allegedly on grounds
that there is no fair justice in Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
A European Union official, Hubert Onidi, who is in charge of
humanitarian aid to African, the Caribbean, and Pacific countries
is said to have conducted a mission in the above camps and found
out that they were unwilling to return to Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Onidi has been quoted by media reports as saying that these
refugees have requested land from Congolese authorities to grow
crops because they are afraid of being repatriated.
</P>
<P>
"The problem with these refugees is that the majority want to
return, but there are ex-FAR -- former Rwandan government
soldiers -- groups intimidating them," Kabaija said.
</P>
<P>
Their repatriation is further crippled by some aid agencies
and international organizations which allegedly want to
perpetuate the refugee problem on unclear motives.
</P>
<P>
"There are sympathetic elements in the international community
which are interested in the perpetuation of the refugee problem
which, for us, would have ended a long time ago," he charged.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of refugees in Congo Brazzaville is made of ex-FAR
and Interahamwe Hutu militia who sided with former Zairean Armed
Forces (FAZ) of late dictator, Mobutu Sese Seko during the
Congolese rebellion last year.
</P>
<P>
Kabaija said that these refugees could have returned home but
aid agencies rather contributed to the flight further west in
providing non-military materials but which were crucial
militarily.
</P>
<P>
Kabaija accuses the ex-FAR and the Hutu militia, together with
these humanitarian organizations of being behind the current
miserable plight of these refugees.
</P>
<P>
There are over 10,000 Rwandan refugees in Congo (B), 3,000 in
the Central African Republic (CAR) and about 20,000 in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Some 800 others who tried to cross to eastern Gabon were
repatriated to Rwanda by the Gabonese authorities who used their
airplanes to air-lift them to Kigali.
</P>
<P>
For Rwandan government officials, all refugees must return
whatever the status they want, and it is essential that all
governments should assist them to resolve this problem.
</P>
<P>
However, U.N. High Commission of Refugees and some agencies
are accused of not providing a helping hand in the matter, and
are said to negotiate asylum for groups of refugees from
northwestern Rwanda, in the districts of Gisenyi and Ruhengeri in
the countries like Central Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
