<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman on US Religion Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said today that China firmly opposes the
attempts of some Western forces to use religious matters as a
means of interfering in other countries' affairs and to make
irresponsible remarks or even malicious attacks on the religious
situation in those countries.
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on a report on world religious issues by an
advisory commission of the U.S. Secretary of State on religious
freedom in foreign countries, Zhu defined China as a country with
a number of religions, noting that Article 36 of the Chinese
Constitution states that its citizens have religious freedom and
that they can freely choose and express their beliefs and make
public their religious status.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are more than 100 million followers of
different religions in China and that the Chinese Government's
religious policy has won the endorsement and support of the broad
masses of the Chinese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
