<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia, Macedonia Sign Joint Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 27 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin and
visiting Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov signed a joint
declaration on friendship and cooperation Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said the two countries intend to take joint
"preventive action" in order to preclude armed action on the
Balkans and in Europe.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony in the Kremlin, Yeltsin said the
foundation for the friendship and fraternity between Russia and
Macedonia had been formed.
</P>
<P>
This document is the first inter-state document signed by the
two countries' leaders, the Russian president said.
</P>
<P>
"We are firmly determined to cultivate our relations on the
basis of equality, non-interference in each other's domestic
affairs, respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity,"
Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov, for his part, said that Russia is among the first to
recognize the Republic of Macedonia and that is "most important"
for the Macedonian people.
</P>
<P>
Recalling the nation's historical friendship with Russia, the
Macedonian president said the Russian and Macedonian peoples were
always close and united by a common history.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov arrived in Moscow on Monday for a two-day visit.
During the visit, the two sides are expected to sign five
inter-governmental agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
