<HEADLINE> Fujian Public Security Forces Rescue Taiwan Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A Taiwanes ship that was caught
in a strong gale in the Taiwan Straits was helped to get to safety
by the public security personnel from China's Fujian Province on
the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The ship was carrying 68 workers to their hometown of Hui'an in
Fujian when it was hit by gale-force winds on the evening of
January 23.
</P>
<P>
When public security's frontier defense troops in the coastal
province heard the distress signal, they responded immediately
with a rescue crew who had to battle the rough winds and heavy
seas, but who managed to finish the job by the next morning.
</P>
<P>
The 68 passengers were then sent on to their hometowns in time
to attend family reunions for the Spring Festival. 
</P>
</TEXT>
