<HEADLINE> Fujian Communist Party Secretary Sends Holiday Greetings To Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Chen Mingyi, the Provincial
Communist Party Secretary of Fujian in southeastern China sent
Spring Festival greetings to Taiwan compatriots today to wish them
a successful and happy new year.
</P>
<P>
This year's Spring Festival, the lunar new year, falls on
Wednesday, the 28th.
</P>
<P>
Chen called 1997 a year of great significance in Chinese
history and said that his province did some remarkable work in its
reforms, opening-up, and economic development last year, and that
it is going through a period of prosperity and social stability,
with the people enjoying a comfortable and happy life.
</P>
<P>
He said that by the end of the century, per capita GNP in
Fujian is expected to be eight times the 1980 level, and by 2010,
the province expects it to be 4 times the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that economic exchanges with Taiwan are
critically important to Fujian's ambitious economic goals, and
that Fujian and Taiwan complement each other in their economies.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has the only special investment zone for Taiwan business
people in the country and is an experimental zone for agricultural
cooperation across the Taiwan Straits, he said, adding that this
year the province will continue to make every effort to improve
its investment environment and safeguard the interests of
investors from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome more Taiwan compatriots to visit Fujian to increase
understanding and trust, and to seek common development with us,"
he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
