<HEADLINE> 2 Million Passengers Safely Leave Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the capital of
China's Guangdong Province, has had about 2 million passengers
moving through its railway station and airport in the past 20 days.
</P>
<P>
Today, the eve of Spring Festival (China's Lunar New Year's
Day), its Baiyuan International Airport had 165 flights and 2,500
passengers.
</P>
<P>
In the past 20 days, there have been 3,350 flights and 457,000
passengers. An airport official says that this was a 6.7 percent
and 2.2 percent increase, respectively, over the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
He said that from January 23 to 25, the daily passenger load
was more than 30,000, a record for domestic airports.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Railway Station had more than 1.5 million
passengers in the 20-day period. From the 23rd to the 26th, its
daily passenger load was 130,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
