<HEADLINE> COSCO Container Transport Company Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo announced the opening of a marine container transport
business in Shanghai's Pudong New Area, today.
</P>
<P>
The China Ocean Shipping Corporation (COSCO) has merged three
container businesses in Tianjin, Shanghai, and Guangzhou to make
the Container Transport Company, with 23 billion yuan (about 2.77
billion US dollars) in capital, a fleet of 140 vessels, and a
combined capacity of 210,000 TEUs.
</P>
<P>
This company ranks fifth in the world, with access to more than
100 major sea ports, said COSCO officials.
</P>
<P>
The company chose to put its headquarters in Shanghai because
it is developing into an international shipping center, Hu Xijie,
vice-minister of communications, explained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
