<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents Say They're Confident about 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey of 500 Beijing
households found that 10.2 percent believed the country's economy
will grow at the same rate as last year, while 78.9 percent said
it will be even faster.
</P>
<P>
Of those questioned, 89.7 percent believed that social security
will be better, while young people and relatively better educated
people tend to have higher expectations for their income.
</P>
<P>
This shows that rapid development has provided more
opportunities for the young and the better educated, according to
an expert. "Thus, the survey indicates that the future Chinese
society will be dominated by the better educated," he said.
</P>
<P>
Among the biggest wishes of many residents for the new year are
health, house and wealth, so the most popular greetings for the
traditional lunar new year's eve this evening is "Wish you good
health, prosperity, and a new house in the new year," according to
the expert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
