<HEADLINE> Foreigners Enjoy Holiday Dinner With Beijing Family </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A Beijing woman, Hu Xiuying,
has invited a group of foreigners to share the family feast in
downtown Beijing for the Chinese lunar New Year's eve.
</P>
<P>
This is the hostess' fifth time to prepare the festival dinner
for foreign tourists. This time, a German woman, one of 33 guests,
could be seen making her first dumpling and displaying it to her
companions and Chinese hosts. "This is equal to your Christmas
Eve," Hu explained, "we always get together to make dumplings,
watch TV, and often stay up all night."
</P>
<P>
Nearly all families in China consider this reunion dinner the
most important festival.
</P>
<P>
Hu's room contained the large Chinese character "Fu," meaning
"good fortune," and the New Year's zodiac sign of the tiger.
</P>
<P>
The Germans announced that the dumplings were delicious, and
that the Chinese family was hospitable. The activity was arranged
by a tourism office specially working with folk customs.
</P>
<P>
Nearly three million overseas tourists visit the Chinese
capital annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
