<HEADLINE> Spring Festival Atmosphere (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Many workers who came to Shenzhen, China's first special
economic zone, from other parts of China, have chosen to remain in
the city during the Spring Festival, which is usually an occasion
for family reunions.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at Shenzhen's labor department, about a
third of the transient workers stay put during the traditional
festival, providing some relief for transportation workers.
</P>
<P>
Employers have planned various kinds of entertainment, and
tourist resorts have cut prices in half, and people working during
the holiday get more pay.
</P>
<P>
Another result has been that many restaurants have signs in
their windows saying, "normal business during Spring Festival."
</P>
<P>
Kunming and Guangzhou Blossom Year Round
</P>
<P>
Kunming, in southwestern China, has been called the "Spring
City" for its pleasant weather all year round, and now more people
buy fresh flowers to decorate their homes.
</P>
<P>
Flowers with symbolic significance are especially popular: young
people buy roses to give to lovers, or buy lilies to send to the
elderly.
</P>
<P>
People from the north like to visit food and amusement fairs,
but in China's southern city of Guangzhou, visiting flower fairs
has become popular.
</P>
<P>
The city's eight districts have large flower fairs, but the
central flower fair is the biggest, covering three blocks with
many visitors and various types of flowers.
</P>
<P>
Flower fairs have enriched people's lives, and provide
opportunities and challenges for businessmen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
