<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A strong rally by gold kept
the Australian dollar above 67 U.S. cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining its 1-U.S.-cent gain made in Asia trading Monday,
the local dollar closed at 67.23 U.S. cents Tuesday, from 65.93
U.S. cents in local trading on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The local dollar was boosted by the improvement in the gold
price, which rose to above 300 U.S. dollars an ounce at the
weekend for the first time in two months.
</P>
<P>
A foreign exchange dealer from National Australia Bank said
gold sent the Australian dollar flying on Friday evening and
bullish sentiment fueled further gains from there.
</P>
<P>
The dealer said the local currency was also supported Tuesday
by heavy North American buying.
</P>
<P>
However, the greenback fell on reports of U.S. President Bill
Clinton's alleged sexual relationship with a former White House
intern.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished the local session at 84.47
Japanese yen, from 83.58 Friday, and at 1.1904 Deutsche marks,
from 1.1892. 
</P>
