<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Visits Southern Chinese Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, the chairman of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee, in a visit to
Guangzhou's Tianhe High-Tech Development Zone on Sunday, said that
Guangdong Province should provide good conditions for the
development of the information industry.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that the high-tech industry plays a very important role
in promoting economic growth and social development and that there
needs to be increased research to develop the information industry.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the importance of software development and the
mastery of advanced foreign technology. He said Guangdong needs to
do more training of people and use the expertise in the industry.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei, a member of the of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee's Political Bureau and the Secretary of Guangdong
Provincial Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, accompanied
Qiao during his visit. 
</P>
