<HEADLINE> Olympic Winner Admits She Took Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic champion Petra
Schneider-Kind admitted when she compted for East Germamy she took
drugs as a teenager.
</P>
<P>
Schneider-Kind, winner of Olympic gold in the 400 meters medley
in 1980 in Moscow under the name of Schneider, said she was first
confronted with the pills when she was 14.
</P>
<P>
"I had no idea what they were. I was told they were vitamin
pills. They were probably Oral-Turinabol," she was quoted as
saying, referring to a banned anabolic.
</P>
<P>
"My performances soon improved dramatically," said Schneider, a
former world champion. "I experienced unnatural muscular growth
and my voice became deeper." 
