<HEADLINE> 20 Million Nigerians Suffer from Goitre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- An estimated 20 million
malnourished Nigerians are currently suffering from endemic
goitre, according the the United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF).
</P>
<P>
As a result of iodine deficiency, some 760 million people
across the world have goitre, a swollen neck disease, UNICEF said
in its report entitled "The State of the World's Children 1998"
available here today.
</P>
<P>
In Nigeria, poverty and lack of child care are principal
causes of malnutrition, which leads to iodine deficiency as well
as mental retardation and stunting.
</P>
<P>
The disease is prevalent in the Middle Belt Region of the
country, one of the poorest going by the World Bank standard,
according to a UNICEF survey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
