<HEADLINE> Macao Governor Announces Donation to Quake-Hit Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
announced on Tuesday that the Macao government will donate one
million patacas (about 125,000 U.S. dollars) to victims of a
strong earthquake in northern China.
</P>
<P>
The donations will be made via the Macao Red Cross, said a
dispatch released on Tuesday by the Government Information Office.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake that rocked the Zhangjiakou area in Hebei
Province earlier this month killed dozens of people and left tens
of thousands of people homeless in biting cold of minus 30 degrees
Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Macao residents have so far donated more than 5 million patacas
(about 625,000 dollars) to the victims via the Xinhua News Agency
Macao Branch.
</P>
<P>
Local charity groups also opened special bank accounts for
donations since the earthquake happened. 
</P>
