<DOCNO> XIE19980127.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria's Abacha to Name New Deputy Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Head of State General
Sani Abacha will soon name a new Chief of General Staff to
replace Lieutenant-General Oladipo Diya, who is now in detention
for alleged complicity in the failed coup plot last December.
</P>
<P>
A Nigerian newspaper, This Day Tuesday quoted a "highly
reliable source" as saying that the new chief of general staff
would most likely come from the navy, which has recently elevated
six Commodores to the rank of Rear Admirals.
</P>
<P>
The chief of staff is the number two leader in the Nigerian
military government, second only to General Sani Abacha, who is
also the Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant-General Diya was appointed the Chief of General
Staff in November 1993 soon after Abacha took over power from the
interim government of Chief Earnest Shonkan.
</P>
<P>
More than 72 military officers as well as civilians have been
arrested in connection with the coup on December 21, 1997. The
government said they will be tried by a martial court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
