<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Bans Illicit Fishing Camps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar authorities
have ordered people who have set up fishing camps at prohibited
beach areas to move away, Daily News said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The order was given following reports that a number of people
have moved into the prohibited areas on the sly for the purpose
of starting fishing camps, Zanzibar West District Commissioner,
Ali Hassan Khamis, said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Khamis as saying that the fishing camps
have been banned in a number of spots for health and security
reasons. The official mentioned the prohibited areas as Kwale,
Tungume, Chukwani Mtoni and Mazizini.
</P>
<P>
It is feared that the establishment of such fishing camps may
lead to the outbreak of cholera and illicit fishing using
explosives in Zanzibar, an archipelago consisted of two big
islands and a number of smaller islands in the Indian Ocean.
</P>
