<HEADLINE> UN Chief to Visit Egypt in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan is due here on February 11 on his first visit to Egypt
since taking post at the world organization.
</P>
<P>
He will meet with President Hosni Mubarak on the peacemaking in
the Middle East and the implementation of the U.N. resolutions on
the decades-long Arab-Israeli conflicts, major local newspapers
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
