international developments and the envisaged U.N. reform including
the expansion of the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Annan's visit to Egypt will be part of a Mideast tour, which
will also take him to Syria, Jordan, Israel and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Annan, working with the U.N. for 30 years, replaced Boutros
Boutros-Ghali to become U.N. chief on January 1, 1997. 
