Chinese New Year which begins Wednesday, to be followed a few days
later by Muslims' Aidil Fitri (Festival of Fast-breaking), would
further enhance goodwill and unity among the various races.
</P>
<P>
It is vital to further promote unity and solidarity as racial
harmony is the nation's strength especially during the current
economic crisis, the Malaysian King said in his Chinese New Year
message.
</P>
<P>
He said the double celebrations served as an excellent time for
the various races to forge closer ties and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The King also called on the people to exercise tolerance and
patience during the economic crisis facing the country.
</P>
<P>
