<HEADLINE> 1.2 Million Farmers Shake Off Poverty in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- More than 1.2 million farmers
in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region shook off
poverty in 1997.
</P>
<P>
This brings the total rural population which have shaken off
poverty to over 11.3 million. The region's poverty-stricken
people had reduced to 3.66 million in 1997 from some 15 million in
1985.
</P>
<P>
So far, 32 out of the 49 poverty-stricken counties in the
region have provided adequate food and clothing for local people.
</P>
<P>
Most of the region's needy population live in mountainous areas
which are suject to natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the region invested more than one billion yuan in
poverty eradication, up 60 percent over the previous year. Most
of the funds was used in helping local farmers plant cash
trees and crops and breeding domestic animals.
</P>
<P>
The region also used large amounts of money in building over
1,400 water supply projects, 4,000 kilometers of highways and
putting up power transmission lines for 24 townships which have no
electricity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
