<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Year of Tiger, Year of Testing for Singaporeans: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong said on the Chinese Lunar New Year's eve on Tuesday that
the year of Tiger will be a testing year for Singaporeans and
called on them to take this turbulence in their stride.
</P>
<P>
In his message to mark the Chinese New Year and Hari Raya
Aidilfitri, the Festival of Fast-Breaking, the prime minister
noted that the regional financial crisis had hit Singapore hard,
as the stock market was down; businessmen were apprehensive; fewer
tourists were arriving in Singapore, and exports to the region
were slowing down.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said that the financial sector will see little
growth in the new year because few projects will seek financing,
little investment money will flow from the developed countries
into Southeast Asia, and there will be less funds to manage out of
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
In the country's key manufacturing sector, investment
commitments will be affected, because some Multi-National
Corporations (MNCs) are re-evaluating planned capital investments,
and may defer or stretch out the projects, he said.
</P>
<P>
Singaporeans, he said, are already feeling the effects, as
their bonuses will be smaller, more workers will be retrenched and
finding new jobs will be more difficult for them. The government
revenues, on the other hand, will be stagnant, which means smaller
budget surplus.
</P>
<P>
Given the testing year ahead, the prime minister called on the
fellow Singaporeans, "We must take this turbulence in our stride"
and "we must rise to the challenge together". "This is a somber
message for all Singaporeans," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the year of Tiger, the government will focus
its spending on items which underpin Singapore's long-term
competitiveness and security, namely, education, economic
infrastructure, and defense, and will trim or defer less essential
projects.
</P>
<P>
Besides, he said Singaporeans will have to keep costs of doing
business down and will have to increase their productivity and
reduce business costs.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also emphasized the importance of continued
training of the workers, as training gives the workers here the
best chance of staying competitive and so keep their jobs, or find
new ones should they be retrenched.
</P>
<P>
Noting that in the lunar calendar, the Tiger personality is
brave, active and enthusiastic, Goh said, "these qualities will
serve us well as we tackle the region's economic crisis and the
ensuing economic and social difficulties."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
