<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 34 points lower at 2,209 with a turnover
of 39 million dollars (23 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares dived 29 cents to 755 cents. Other main leaders
to fall were Brierley Investment, easing 2c to 117c, Carter Holt
Harvey, losing 8c to 266c and Lion Nathan, dropping 1c to 431c.
</P>
<P>
Leaders to gain included Air New Zealand, up 3c to 311c, and
Fletcher Forest and Fletcher Paper each rose 1c to 132c and 233c
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the market tone was steady with rises and falls
equaled at 41 apiece. The smaller companies index managed to rise
slightly despite the fall in the main leaders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
