<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Add 100 Kilometers of High-Grade Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
industrial and commercial center, plans to build another 100
kilometers of high-grade highways this year.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the city has invested 12 billion yuan
(1.44 billion US dollars) to build and improve a number of
high-grade roads, including the Shanghai section of the
Shanghai-Nanjing Expressway and the Pudong section of the Inner
Ring Road.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's highway system currently stretches a total of 3,880
kilometers, with high-grade roads accounting for 20.92 percent of
the total, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
To woven the city's highway network, which features three ring
roads and ten radiating roads from the city center, Shanghai will
see the completion of a 20-km section of Shanghai-Hangzhou
Expressway this year, said the officials. 
