<HEADLINE> Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone Witnesses Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone,
the first zone of its kind in China, recored a 1997 economic
growth rate of 23.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao Zone, located in Shanghai's New Pudong Area, ended
the year with a Gross Domestic Product (GDP) of 5.09 billion yuan
(613 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The zone's foreign trade volume reached 2.767 billion US
dollars, up 62.5 percent on 1996. The figure included exports of
720 million US dollars, up 113.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The local government attributed the achievements to the fact
tariff exemptions for export processing, cargo transferrals and
storage in the zone helped firms cut costs and increase profits.
</P>
<P>
Improved infrastructure and services also helped the zone
attract additional resident enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao Port provided the zone with convenient transport
facilities, and handled 4.76 million tons of cargo in 1997, up
24.6 percent on the year before.
</P>
<P>
The zone, which covers 6.4 sq.km., has attracted 3,144
overseas-funded projects involving total investments of 3.8
billion US dollars.  
</P>
