<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- US-based Praxair Corporation
has signed an agreement to invest in an infrastructure project to
produce solid-state carbon dioxide in central-south China's Hunan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the solely foreign-funded project will begin in
the near future in the Yueyang Economic and Technological
Development Zone.
</P>
