<HEADLINE> OSCE Security Seminar Begins in Vienna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Senior officers from all the 54
members of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe
(OSCE) gathered here on Monday for a three-day seminar on European
security policies.
</P>
<P>
The seminar brought together officers including United States
Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Henry Shelton, Chief of
General Staff of Russia's Armed Forces Anatoly Kvashnin, and Klaus
Naumann, chairman of the Military Committee of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is designed to discuss the development of a
European security environment and its impact on defense policies
and military reforms.
</P>
<P>
Naumann told reporters that he believed the seminar will
improve mutual trust between the member countries.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was proposed by Russia, which is trying to enforce
the organization's role. The OSCE is the only security
organization in Europe that Russia has joined.
</P>
<P>
The organization was first set up in 1972 as a forum for
political dialogue and negotiation but its role was expanded after
the disintegration of the Soviet Union in 1991. It brought
together all the European countries and Canada and the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
