<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Presidential Candidates Begin Debate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, January 26 (xinhua) -- Costa Rica's two leading
presidential candidates will start a debate Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Social Christian Unity Party (PUSC) candidate, Miguel Angel
Rodriguez, has been far ahead of his rival Jose Miguel Corrales,
of the governing National Liberation Party (PLN), the latest polls
showed.
</P>
<P>
This debate is a prolongation of the electoral campaigns, which
officially concluded last weekend.
</P>
