president, two vice presidents, 57 senators and representatives
for Costa Rica's 81 municipalities in the general election to be
held on February 1.
</P>
<P>
The PLN holds 28 seats (one less than an absolute majority) in
Senate, the PUSC 25 and three other parties four seats.
</P>
<P>
The new president will take office on May 8 for a four-year
term. 
