<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Technological Export Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's major
business hub, set a record technological export value of 664
million US dollars in 1997, up 23.6 percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The substantial increase was attributed to the expansion of
export channels for new and high technology products, according to
International Business Daily.
</P>
<P>
The city exported more than 300 varieties of related products,
with the export volume rising by 37 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports of infrared sensors manufactured in the city accounted
for 70 percent of total sales on the world market.
</P>
<P>
The city exported cesium iodide crystals valued at more than 50
million US dollars to the United States and Japan. 
