from Inter for the talented player.
</P>
<P>
Sousa, 27, had a contract with the European Cup winners running
until July 1999, had already signed a contract with Inter starting
in July.
</P>
<P>
Dortmund, which is a disppointing 10th in the Bundesliga, was
reluctunt to release Sousa previously but changed its mind when
Inter made a bid of 15 million marks (8.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sousa, who moved to Dortmund from Juventus in July 1996 in a
4.2 million U.S. dollars, underwent surgery on his knee soon after
the transferring, and played only 26 league games since.
</P>
<P>
He helped his new-signed club to last May's European Cup
victory over old club Juventus, becoming the only player ever to
win consecutive European Cups with different clubs. The Turin side
won the trophy in 1996. 
