<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economy in Southern Fujian Province of China Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The "Gold Triangle Area" in
southern Fujian province, east China, have emerged as one of
China's most developed areas.
</P>
<P>
The area, which includes the cities of Xiamen, Quanzhou and
Zhangzhou, is the native place of many overseas Chinese and home
to 80 percent of the Taiwanese.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that per-capita gross domestic product (GDP) in
Xiamen reached 27,700 yuan (3,462 U.S. dollars) last year. And the
city has more than 60 industrial enterprises with an annual output
value of over 100 million yuan (12.5 million U.S. dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen has become one of the country's important ports. It has
utilized 6.3 billion U.S. dollars of overseas investment in the
past five years. It ranks fourth in the country in export valume
and 50 percent of the city's industrial products are exported.
</P>
<P>
The annual average growth rate of GDP in Quanzhou, an ancient
trade hub, was 42.9 percent during the 1993-97 period. The city
has set up 21 large industrial development zones and approved more
than 4,000 overseas-funded projects, with a combined actually used
overseas fund of 3.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Quanzhou has made great efforts to develop township-run
enterprises in the fields of garments, shoes, china and stone
carving. Output value of the township-run enterprises in the city
reached 100 billion yuan (12.5 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997,
ranking first in the province.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou, a leading agricultural city in Fujian, has
introduced a total of 4.88 billion U.S. dollars in overseas
investment from 1993 to October, 1997, of which 1.9 billion
U.S. dollars were utilized.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city has established 10 development zones and
introduced 580 overseas-funded projects with a total contractual
investment of 1.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The improved investment environment in the "Gold Triangle Area"
has helped absorb more overseas investors and push forward its
export-oriented economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980127.0233 </DOCNO>
