<HEADLINE> Ankara Fined for Crowd Bad Behaviour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Turk Telekom was fined 44,300
U.S. dollars on Monday and ordered to play its next two games
behind closed doors because crowd trouble at its last Euroleague
basketball game.
</P>
<P>
FIFA, world basketball governing body, said in a statement on
Monday from Munich of Germany that the Turkish team lost the
January 22 match against Olympiakos of Greece 80-82 but the game
was marred by crowd misbehaviour.
</P>
<P>
