<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
The Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- New Philippine Senate President Neptali Gonzales Vowed
Monday to expedite the passage of the Ramos administration's
priority measures, including the heavily amended 1997 Down-stream
Oil Industry Deregulation Act.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine government Monday moved to avert the possible
escalation of clashes between the government forces and the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) by ordering the government
negotiation team to meet with its MILF counterpart and settle the
dispute.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippines is set to stay a little longer under the
tutelage of the International Monetary Fund rather than exit early
and enter into a "precautionary arrangement" that would not give
an entirely clean bill of health before investors.  
</P>
