<HEADLINE> Indonesian Grand Prix Removed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian motorcycling
grand prix was removed from the calender for economic reasons, the
International Motorcycling Federation (FIM) announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian grand prix, originally slated for March 29 in
Shah Alam, will step into the space left by the cancellation of
the Indonesian race in April and switched to a new circuit in
Johor.
</P>
<P>
The change in venues will not be confirmed until the work on
the track acquired by the FIM has been done.
</P>
<P>
FIM The Portuguese grand prix was cancelled last month for the
yet completed safety work on the Estoril track.
</P>
<P>
A replacement for the Portuguese grand prix was still under
investigation, FIM said.
</P>
<P>
The following is the revised grand prix schedule:
</P>
<P>
April 5 Japan, Suzuk
</P>
<P>
April 19  Malaysia, Johor (to be confirmed)
</P>
<P>
May 3 Spain, Jerez de la Frontera
</P>
<P>
May 17  Italy, Mugello
</P>
<P>
May 31  France, Paul Ricard
</P>
<P>
June 14 to be announced
</P>
<P>
June 27 Netherlands, Assen
</P>
<P>
July 5  Britain, Donington Park
</P>
<P>
July 19 Germany, Sachsentring (to be confirmed)
</P>
<P>
