<HEADLINE> Ecuadoran Acting President Visits Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran Acting President
Fabian Alarcon Monday urged the guarantor nations of the Rio de
Janeiro Protocol to help solve the border disputes between Ecuador
and Peru.
</P>
<P>
Following his meeting with his Argentine counterpart Carlos
Menem, Alarcon told a press conference that he hoped Argentina
will continue to assist his country.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon made a brief visit to Argentina to thank Menem for the
work carried out by Argentina as a guarantor of the Rio de Janeiro
Protocol.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, Chile and the United States are also guarantors of the
Rio Protocol.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador and Peru had bloody clashes in the border area in
January 1995 and reached a ceasefire agreement two months
later. Since then, the two nations had held several rounds of
talks on a permanent solution to the decades-old border dispute.
</P>
</TEXT>
