<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Council Members of German-Czech Future Fund Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Germany and the
Czech Republic today announced the composition of the governing
council of the German-Czech Future Fund in a bid to start concrete
projects mainly to help some 8,000 Czech victims of German Nazi
brutality.
</P>
<P>
With the appointment of five representatives from each side,
the council could now start to use the fund to finance projects to
help Nazi victims in the Czech Republic as well as to promote
youth exchanges, scientific and environmental cooperation, and
preservation of historical sites, the German government said.
</P>
<P>
Germany is to provide the fund with 140 million marks (80
million U.S. dollars) while the Czech Republic is due to come up
with an additional 25 million marks (about 14 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The fund is set up under the German-Czech reconciliation accord
signed in January 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
