<DOCNO> XIE19980127.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Ban on Handguns Comes Into Effect in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- A full ban on handguns came into
force in Britain today and anyone caught to have pistol with him
could have maximum 10-year imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
Junior Home Office Minister Alun Michael said today Britain now
"has some of the toughest gun laws in the world."
</P>
<P>
The firearms legislation was introduced after the 1996 Dunblane
massacre when crazed Thomas Hamilton shot dead 16 schoolchildren
and their teacher before killing himself.
</P>
<P>
Owners of handguns of 0.22 caliber or less now have until the
end of February to hand in their weapons in return for
compensation or face draconian punishment. All guns over 0.22
caliber were supposed to have been surrendered last year.
</P>
<P>
"Following the successful removal last year of large-caliber
handguns, this second hand-in will fulfill the government's
commitment to improving public safety by removing the remaining
small-caliber handguns," Michael said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Around 116,000 large-caliber and 26,000 small-caliber weapons
have already been handed in. Officials expect another 10,000
small-caliber weapons to be surrendered by the end of February.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
